\f1\b\fs32 ground connection
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f2\fs32  provides an alternate path for electrical currents to flow back to the source. Ashore, electrical circuits are grounded by connecting them electrically to a rod or pipe driven into the earth, while aboard ship, a connection the hull serves the same purpose.    A 
